-- HSBC Sells 230 Billion Rupiah of 6.75% Uridashi Notes
-- B y   H a r u m i   I c h i k u r a
-- 2012-01-24T15:32:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-24/hsbc-sells-230-billion-rupiah-of-6-75-uridashi-notes.html
The following uridashi bond went
on sale. Uridashi bonds are debt issued in the euromarket
and sold mainly to Japanese individual investors.  Issuer:              HSBC Bank plc
Amount:              230,000 million Indonesia Rupiah
Coupon:              6.75 percent
Duration:            Five years
Sales period:        Jan. 19 - Feb. 15
Settlement date:     Feb. 17, 2012
Maturity:            Feb. 17, 2017
Uridashi Manager:    Hinode Securities Co.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Harumi Ichikura in London at   hichikura@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  